cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.FL, cs.SE 

This paper deals with the analysis of logic programs, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The use of abstract interpretation and labelling functions also suggests a connection to logic and constraint programming (cs.LO), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of unification, which is a fundamental operation in formal language theory and automata (cs.FL). Finally, the paper discusses the generalization of previous works, which suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE) and the development of reusable techniques.
